bio.experienceSummary:
I am excited about fostering children's growth and dedicated to providing reliable childcare and tutoring for families. In addition to working in offices, I have babysat and tutored on the side. I am passionate about the wellbeing and safety of all children. I'm patient, calm, and creative, and I love playing board games, puzzles. I am skilled in spelling, grammar, reading comprehension, and essay writing.

I believe in open and honest communication with parents and will always keep them updated about their child's day and any issues that arise. I am very comfortable enforcing household rules to ensure a safe and structured environment. 

My college degree (BA in English and Literature) and being bilingual and biliterate in English and Spanish have given me the tools needed to help kids learn and thrive in their education. I can comfortably care for two children at a time, and I have experience with children aged 3-15.

description.originalText: Harper is an amazing babysitter! She watched our two children from toddler to elementary school age, and we wished she still lived close by. She engaged them in age appropriate activities and games, read to them, took them to the park and helped with meals. She is reliable, caring and calm, and I wouldnâ€™t hesitate to recommend her to other families for babysitting or tutoring.

bio.experienceSummary: I have over 10 years of experience. I can help with Travel and Errands. I actually work for the city school district as a special education aide So I have classroom experience as well as full time nanny experience. I am currently looking for a full or part time nanny job. I am a Highly-motivated and enthusiastic bi-lingual individual eager to take on new challenges. Excellent leadership skills with strong communication skills. Highly organized with superior attention to details. Responsible, dependable, and trustworthy. Compassionate, empathetic, and caring. I am fully vaccinated not boosted but don't mind getting the booster shot You will not regret the decision of having me on your team!

Hello!

My name is Emily and my background is in education as I have a Masters Degree in Childhood Special Education with a focus in Learning Disabilities and an Undergraduate Degree in Early Childhood General and Special Education with a concentration in Human Development and English. I'm currently the assistant director of the Sarah Lawrence Graduate Teaching Program and teach courses on Neurodiversity and Special Education, Curriculum, and a Practicum course. I have ample experience babysitting and tutoring ages 2-12 but am open to all ages! 

When caring for children, I enjoy spending time outdoors and engaging in activities that spark their creativity. It is important for the child to feel safe, comfortable, and most importantly have fun! 

My passions include art, nature and animals. My professional interests include Emotionally Responsive Practice, Emergent Curriculum, and a strengths based perspective.

Hi! I am 26 years old and a registered nurse. I graduated in December 2022 from Felician University; I have an additional bachelor's degree in biology from Fordham University. I am a nurse at a Pediatric officer in Hoboken working 8-5:30 Monday to Friday. Looking to fill some of my nights and weekends with babysitting!
 
I have babysat since I was the age of 14 and I have experience babysitting kids of every age with a consistent babysitting job for the past 3 years with a family with 4 kids aged 4months-9 as well as a family for 2 years with one kid aged 2. I grew up babysitting three younger sisters and cousins as well. I am CPR certified in addition to being a registered nurse. I am really great with kids and love being with them. I have my own transportation.

*Vaccinated for COVID-19*
I have over a decade of experience working with children in the Department of Education. I also have a very strong background working with children who have various special needs.

Hi, my name is Angelee, I'm 24 years old. I'm very patient and attentive. I prioritize creating a safe, engaging environment where kids can thrive. I have extensive experience and a genuine passion for nurturing children and guiding them through life. As a nanny, I tailor each day to meet the unique needs and interests of your child, ensuring they enjoy our time while learning and growing. My most recent job, I worked with a family of two boys (3 and 12), and a 4month old girl where I managed the kids' daily routines (from meals to homework to bed/bath time), helped around the house, and took them on fun educational trips. I loved teaching them Spanish and Italian, too! I strive to provide the highest level of care! Let's work together to support your child's development in a warm, loving atmosphere. Feel free to reach out in any case, I am flexible! References available.

description.originalText: Angelee has been an amazing nanny for our 5 and 6-year-olds over the past seven months. She quickly bonded with them, and they absolutely adore her! She goes above and beyond by planning fun, educational activities and providing loving, dependable care. Her professionalism and kindness have made her a true part of our family. I highly recommend her to any family looking for a caring and dedicated nanny!

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm passionate about caring for children and helping them grow and develop. With over a year of experience as a childcare provider, I pride myself on being patient, creative, and approachable. I ensure open communication with parents, whether it's through regular updates or following their preferred method.

I'm comfortable enforcing household rules and enjoy playing various games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games. I'm more than happy to lend a hand with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, light housekeeping, travel, and swimming supervision.

I'm certified in CPR training and am always seeking opportunities to enhance my skills. I'm comfortable caring for up to three children of various age groups, and am confident I can provide a safe and nurturing environment for your little ones. Let's connect and explore how I can be a valuable asset to your family!

Hello!
 My name is Beatrice, I am a 25-year-old artist and folk musician. I've lived in Brooklyn for about 3 years now and love it. I am originally from Portland, Oregon and have previously lived in France where I was an au pair in my later teen years. I work part time in a hotel bar and am looking for more work during this slow season. 
 I have 10+ years of experience in childcare, covering a full spectrum of needs and expectations. I have cared for newborns and their cheeky toddler-tween siblings and cared for children with special needs one on one. I'm always excited to share my interests in art and music with the children I'm taking care of and learning about what they are interested in and what they are curious about.
 I am open to the occasional babysitting, errand running, child commuting, weekly help, and can be flexible with varied weeks. 
 Please feel free to message me with any questions- would love to chat!

I'm a patient and caring childcare professional with over 12 years of caregiving experience. I've cared for children of all ages, from infants to teenagers. After spending over 4 years working as an editor and writer in the field of corporate communications, I've transitioned to supporting kids and families again as a caregiver. I'm enrolled in a graduate degree program at Sarah Lawrence College where I am working towards my Master's in Fine Arts (MFA) in Creative Writing. I'm passionate about education and creativity, and I'm eager to support kids and families by combining my love for fostering healthy childhood development with my experience as a teacher, tutor, and writer. My goal is to be a creative writing educator, specifically working with young children and adolescents to help them discover the joy of writing and reading poetry. I am fully vaccinated with the Pfizer vaccine.

description.originalText: Katelyn has been sitting for our young preschool-aged child regularly for the past year and has done a great job. She's communicative, reliable and trustworthy and our kid has a great time with her!

bio.experienceSummary:
Making quick connections with children is my specialty, allowing them (and their grownups) to feel safe and secure with a new sitter. Available for a one time night out, as a semi-regular sitter or part-time summer work.

I offer over 15 years of caring for children professionally. Working with children is the most rewarding job I can imagine and I consider it a privilege to be able to do so. I am a lead teacher at a well respected preschool in Manhattan, graduating soon with a master's degree in Early Childhood Education and have a bachelors degree in psychology. I understand how impactful play is to the development of children, and am engaged, present and always looking for opportunities to play with intention. I'm not afraid to get on the floor and be silly, play hide and seek for hours and I have the recipe for homemade play dough memorized. I have professionally cared for newborns as young as 2 weeks, senior citizens with special need and all ages in between.
